        <mxCell id="osm3N-SdJkY_QjZSTnFf-31" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Main Thread&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;The main thread sits and waits for a shutdown message, and if found, does a graceful shutdown, including an announcement to go offline to HA/ECHONET. If IO threads see this, then should shut down.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Do we need one IO thread with async events on, or multiple IO threads for different parts?&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="50" y="145" width="280" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
